{
  "id": "phase-rs_phase_2691",
  "repo_name": "phase-rs/phase",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/phase-rs/phase",
  "base_commit": "eb4d2ba0681649d83f5077f0770be089dce8eced",
  "pr_number": 2691,
  "issue_number": 2690,
  "issue_title": "[Card Bug] Exile-base cumulative upkeep is parsed but never synthesized or payable",
  "issue_body": "## Card(s)\nThought Lash; any card whose cumulative upkeep cost is an exile cost, especially \"Cumulative upkeep-Exile the top card of your library.\"\n\n## Build/version\n`phase-rs/phase` upstream `main` at `35d74b17`\n\n## Game mode\nAI / engine\n\n## Actual behavior\n`Cumulative upkeep` is implemented for several base cost shapes, but exile-base costs are still treated as unsupported:\n\n- `parse_cumulative_upkeep_keyword` can produce `Keyword::CumulativeUpkeep(AbilityCost::Exile { ... })`.\n- `AbilityCost::supports_cumulative_upkeep_payment` returns `false` for `AbilityCost::Exile`.\n- `database::synthesis` only emits a `PayCumulativeUpkeep` trigger when the cost is supported, so these cards receive no cumulative-upkeep trigger at all.\n- `game::coverage` has a regression test that intentionally reports `Keyword:CumulativeUpkeepUnsupportedCost` for an exile-base cumulative upkeep cost.\n\nThat means Thought Lash does not get the core upkeep trigger: it will not gain age counters, it will not ask the controller to exile the top card of their library once per age counter, and it will not sacrifice itself when that cost is declined or cannot be paid.\n\n## Expected behavior\nCR 702.24a says cumulative upkeep means:\n\n1. At the beginning of the permanent's controller's upkeep, put an age counter on it.\n2. Then that player may pay the listed upkeep cost for each age counter on it.\n3. If the player does not pay, sacrifice the permanent.\n\nFor Thought Lash-style costs, the per-counter cost should expand from:\n\n```rust\nAbilityCost::PerCounter {\n    counter: CounterType::Age,\n    target: SelfRef,\n    base: AbilityCost::Exile {\n        count: 1,\n        zone: Some(Zone::Library),\n        filter: None,\n    },\n}\n```\n\ninto an interactive payment of N top cards from the controller's library, where N is the number of age counters on the source at trigger resolution.\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n1. Build a face with:\n\n```rust\nKeyword::CumulativeUpkeep(AbilityCost::Exile {\n    count: 1,\n    zone: Some(Zone::Library),\n    filter: None,\n})\n```\n\n2. Run `database::synthesis::synthesize_face`.\n3. Observe that no `TriggerMode::PayCumulativeUpkeep` trigger is installed because `supports_cumulative_upkeep_payment()` rejects the cost.\n4. Alternatively, call `game::coverage::card_face_gaps`; it reports `Keyword:CumulativeUpkeepUnsupportedCost`.\n5. Put a Thought Lash-like permanent onto the battlefield and advance to its controller's upkeep.\n\nExpected:\n\n- The upkeep trigger is created.\n- One age counter is placed on the permanent.\n- The controller can pay by exiling one top library card per age counter.\n- Declining or being unable to pay sacrifices the permanent.\n\nActual:\n\n- The exile-base cumulative upkeep ability is omitted before runtime, so no trigger or payment happens.\n\n## Impact\nThis is a real card-behavior bug, not only a coverage-reporting gap. Thought Lash's main balancing cost is missing, and any future card data with exile-base cumulative upkeep will silently lose its upkeep obligation.\n\nIt also leaves the cumulative-upkeep implementation incomplete despite the engine already supporting many related pieces:\n\n- `AbilityCost::PerCounter`\n- `Effect::ExileTop`\n- library-zone cost parsing for \"exile the top card of your library\"\n- cumulative-upkeep trigger synthesis\n- unless-payment prompts\n- sacrifice-on-decline resolution\n\n## Suggested fix\nAdd exile-base cumulative upkeep support end to end.\n\n1. Extend the cumulative-upkeep support boundary:\n   - Allow `AbilityCost::Exile { zone: Some(Zone::Library), filter: None, ... }` in `AbilityCost::supports_cumulative_upkeep_payment`.\n   - Keep unsupported exile shapes rejected unless the payment path can handle them safely.\n\n2. Expand `PerCounter` correctly:\n   - Scale `AbilityCost::Exile { count, zone: Some(Zone::Library), filter: None }` by the age-counter count.\n   - Preserve the library source so the payment is top-of-library exile, not arbitrary card choice.\n\n3. Add a payable unless-cost path:\n   - Surface an `UnlessPayment` / payment prompt for exiling N top cards from the controller's library.\n   - If the library has fewer than N cards, the payment is unpayable and the permanent is sacrificed.\n   - If payment succeeds, move exactly the top N cards to exile and suppress the sacrifice branch.\n\n4. Keep existing behavior for supported costs:\n   - Mana, pay-life, sacrifice, discard, all-mana `OneOf`, and all-mana `Composite` cumulative upkeep paths should remain unchanged.\n\n5. Update coverage:\n   - Remove the `Keyword:CumulativeUpkeepUnsupportedCost` gap for supported top-library exile cumulative upkeep.\n   - Keep coverage tests for truly unsupported exile shapes if needed.\n\n## Tests\nAdd focused tests around the existing cumulative-upkeep suite:\n\n- Parser/type sanity: Thought Lash text parses to `Keyword::CumulativeUpkeep(AbilityCost::Exile { zone: Some(Zone::Library), count: 1, ... })`.\n- Synthesis: an exile-base cumulative upkeep keyword installs exactly one `PayCumulativeUpkeep` trigger.\n- Runtime payment: with one age counter, accepting the payment exiles the top card of the controller's library and keeps the permanent.\n- Runtime scaling: with two age counters, accepting exiles exactly two top cards.\n- Failure/decline: declining the prompt sacrifices the permanent.\n- Unpayable: if the controller has fewer library cards than the required count, the permanent is sacrificed.\n- Coverage: supported top-library exile cumulative upkeep no longer reports `Keyword:CumulativeUpkeepUnsupportedCost`.\n\n## Components\n- `crates/engine/src/types/ability.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/database/synthesis.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/game/effects/mod.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/game/engine_payment_choices.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/game/coverage.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_special.rs`\n- `crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_cost.rs`\n\n## Token-score fit\nThis should be a strong token-score candidate because the PR would not be a tiny parser-only patch. A proper fix touches typed cost support, cumulative-upkeep synthesis, per-counter cost expansion, interactive unless-payment resolution, top-of-library exile movement, coverage, and engine tests.\n\nThe implementation surface is comparable to the better-scoring runtime PRs: it crosses parser, database synthesis, game state/payment flow, and tests, while staying narrowly scoped to one CR-backed bug.",
